Minutes Of the By-Laws Review Committee held 11/16/98

Tony opened the meeting at 5:35 pm

Members present :
Tony Z, Jonathan B, Chris W, Nila A., Mike B, Melissa K, Johanna T, Jennifer
S, John B, Katie T, Matthew G, Matthew C, Joseph H, Matthew D, Erica T.
{{again if I missed someone, let me know..}}

Tony outlined the procedure for voting and discussion, as well outlining the
3 different actions the committee could take on the proposals.
		-Pass with Recommendation
		-Pass without Recommendation
		-Table 

Joseph Hausmann was appointed to take minutes at the Committee meetings


	Proposal #1 from: Matthew Grabowski

Discussion : Barlow, Mattyg, Katie, Nila, Joseph, Jo.

Passed with recomendation 11-3-1

Proposal:
	Change last sentence Article 1 Section 5 to read;

"The voting procedure will be conducted by secret ballot and the vote will
be counted by two (2) members of the Membership Committee as well as one (1)
graduating senior whom does not serve on either the Membership Committee or
the Executive Committee."


	Proposal #2 from: Matthew Grabowski

Discussion: Mattg, Erica, Jen, Missy, Nila, Joe, Mike, Jo, Katie

Passed with recommendation 10-3-2	

Proposal:
	Change Article 1 Section 6 Line 6 to read:

"...least sixteen (16) hours of service work, of which no more than four
(4)...."



	Proposal #3 from: Kathryn Thorsen

Discussion: Barlow, Katie, Erica, Mattg, Bruno, Joseph

motion to table indefinitely passed 12-0-3

Proposal:
	To long to type out, but will be attached when I can get a copy from
Katie.  It added the concept of an "associate member" to the list of
conditions of member status

At 6:25 the meeting was adjourned, to reconviene Monday 5:30 pm HL 218


Respectfully submitted

		Joseph Hausmann

